value.title: Consulting firm scrubs Wiki page of Biden’s COVID-19 czar: report
value.excerpt: The Wikipedia page for President-elect Joe Biden’s new Covid czar Jeff Zients has been scrubbed of material that could portray him as not progressive enough, Politico first reported.

value.title: Pence says US 'a week and a half away' from 'likely approval' of first coronavirus vaccine
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence said Friday that the U.S. is “maybe just a week and a half away” from the “likely approval” of the first vaccine to protect against the novel coronavirus.

value.title: Videos, virtual events and planned trips: Biden, Obama, Pence, Trump weigh in on Georgia runoffs
value.excerpt: President Trump, his predecessor and soon-to-be successor in the White House, as well as Vice President Mike Pence, are all weighing in on Georgia’s two Jan. 5 Senate runoff elections, where the Republican majority in the chamber is up for grabs.

value.title: Republicans demand probe into Padilla's $35M grant to Biden-linked firm, claim 'misuse' of taxpayer funds
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Republicans on the House Oversight and House Administration Committees are demanding answers from California Secretary of State Alex Padilla, who has emerged the frontrunner to be appointed to Vice President-elect Kamala Harris’ Senate seat, about a “highly questionable” $35 million contract

value.title: Trump campaign, RNC raise $207.5 million since Election Day
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: The Trump campaign, the Republican National Committee, their joint-fundraising committees and President Trump’s new PAC Save America raised a whopping $207.5 million since Election Day, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Former Reagan campaign director Ed Rollins slams pro-Trump attorney as 'glorified ambulance chaser'
value.excerpt: Former Reagan campaign director Ed Rollins slammed President Trump's formal and allied legal teams on Fox News Radio's "The Brian Kilmeade Show" Thursday, at one point calling attorney Lin Wood a "glorified ambulance chaser."

value.title: Ratcliffe urges Biden to let Durham probe run its course, says more docs 'should be' declassified
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe on Thursday urged President-elect Joe Biden to allow Special Counsel John Durham's investigation into the origins of the Russia probe to run its course, while saying he hopes there will be "folks held accountable that should be."

value.title: Trump Administration Claims Facebook Improperly Reserved Jobs for H-1B Workers
value.excerpt: A Justice Department lawsuit accuses the social-media company of illegally reserving high-paying jobs for immigrant workers it was sponsoring for permanent residence and failing to adequately search for U.

value.title: Lou Holtz calls Trump ‘greatest president in my lifetime,’ accepts Medal of Freedom
value.excerpt: President Trump on Thursday awarded Notre Dame’s legendary former football coach Lou Holtz the Presidential Medal of Freedom — and Holtz reciprocated by hailing Trump as the “greatest

value.title: Kennedy: Democrats, some Republicans 'have their bowels in an uproar' over Trump not conceding
value.excerpt: Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., said President Trump had every right to contest the results of the 2020 election in an appearance on "America's Newsroom."

value.title: Comey to teach at Columbia Law School alongside professor who leaked Trump memo
value.excerpt: Ex-FBI chief to teach a seminar called “Lawyers and Leaders.”

value.title: Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham turned down Biden administration post, sources say
value.excerpt: The Democratic governor of New Mexico is rumored to be a contender for a separate position in the administration.

value.title: Pro-Trump attorneys Sidney Powell, Lin Wood urge Georgians not to vote in Senate runoffs without changes
value.excerpt: Powell and Wood are not working for the Trump campaign in an official capacity.

value.title: Biden’s stern warning: ‘You cannot be traveling during … holidays’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says he doesn’t “want to scare anybody,” but he’s pleading with Americans to not travel during the upcoming holiday season.

value.title: Biden DHS pick had 'inappropriate' involvement in drug trafficker's commutation: Investigation
value.excerpt: Alejandro Mayorkas has admitted to making a mistake in weighing in on the case.

value.title: Obama accuses Republicans of 'bait-and-switch' on deficit, urges 'bold government steps' from Biden
value.excerpt: Former President Obama argued on Wednesday that Republicans would hypocritically warn about the fiscal impact of economic recovery proposals after passing deficit-inducing tax cuts under President Trump.

value.title: NAACP warns Biden over Rahm Emanuel rumors
value.excerpt: The NAACP became the latest progressive group to warn President-elect Joe Biden against adding former Chicago Mayor Rahm Emanuel to his Cabinet.

value.title: John Mulaney says he was investigated by the Secret Service over joke 'that was not about Donald Trump'
value.excerpt: John Mulaney says he was investigated by the Secret Service after making a joke that many believed was a threat against President Donald Trump.

value.title: Top pro-GOP PAC launching new initiative to counter Biden's 'far-left policies'
value.excerpt: A leading outside group that supports Republican causes is firing up a new initiative to counter what it says will be the "far-left policies" of President-elect Joe Biden's incoming administration.

value.title: Biden should pull off executive order 'blitz' before people can react, leftists say
value.excerpt: Some on the left are suggesting President-elect Joe Biden should sign executive orders and ram through policies as soon as possible -- before the media can fully cover things and give leeway for backlash.

value.title: Obama suggests Trump's 'stereotypical macho style' appealed to some young Black voters
value.excerpt: Former President Obama said President Trump’s “stereotypical macho style” was to blame for his increase in Black male voters this election cycle.

value.title: CNN has been ‘overwhelmingly biased’ against Trump: Joe Concha
value.excerpt: You don't need behind-the-scenes tapes to know that CNN is anti-Trump because of how blatant the network coverage is, Fox News contributor Joe Concha told "America's Newsroom" Wednesday.

value.title: Biden admits Dems 'forgot' rural America, says he did 'something good for the country' by beating Trump
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said Democrats "forgot" rural America in an interview with New York Times opinion columnist Thomas L. Friedman published Wednesday.

value.title: Top Ga. voting official slams threats on election officers, tells Trump, senators to condemn it: 'Has to stop'
value.excerpt: A top Georgia voting official on Tuesday in a fiery press conference decried threats against Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger, the secretary's wife, and other elections officials and workers as the Trump campaign continues to fight the result of the presidential election in court.

value.title: Brad Parscale accuses 'D-level' 'talking heads' around Trump for forcing him out of 2020 campaign
value.excerpt: Former Trump 2020 campaign manager Brad Parscale has accused "D-level" "talking heads" in the president's orbit of starting a whisper campaign that forced him out earlier this year.

value.title: Biden shows off walking boot for first time since injury, says he feels 'good'
value.excerpt: He is expected to wear the boot for several weeks during his recovery.

value.title: GOP senators find bodybags with anti-Trump notes on their front porches
value.excerpt: Several GOP Senators were bombarded with dozens of bodybags at their homes on Tuesday by angry protesters pushing for COVID-19 relief after months of gridlock over negotiations in Congress.

value.title: Biden says coronavirus relief package during lame-duck period likely 'just a start'
value.excerpt: Lawmakers have just days to reach an agreement on additional relief before Congress closes for the year.

value.title: Biden pick for OMB director will push globalist policies that cost US jobs: Huckabee
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s pick for director of the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) will push globalist policies that will lead to the loss of U.S. jobs, former Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee warned Tuesday.

value.title: Cuomo warns that Trump vaccination plans fail minorities, undocumented immigrants
value.excerpt: New York Democratic Gov. Andrew Cuomo penned a letter Tuesday calling for U.S. Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar to alter the upcoming vaccination program he says is inadequately serving "Black, Brown, Asian and low-income communities."
